In a blender or food processor, whip the yolks until pale. about 1 minute. With the motor running. slowly drizzle in the olive oil in a very slow stream. until the mayonnaise begins to emulsify. As it thickens. add a few drops of water to loosen the texture, up to 2 tablespoons if necessary. Add lemon juice 10 taste and season with salt and pepper. Transfer the mayonnaise to a glass or plastic container with a tight lid. The mayonnaise can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.